result.execSummary:
The defendant Cornell Prince Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery of a Financial Institution, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.87.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (32 pages) SENTENCING HEARING, commencing NOVEMBER 3, 2015, received and filed.
Correction made to the victim's name on sentencing dated November 3, 2015, was entered as Amanda B. should have been Andrea B.

Defendant Cornell Prince in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Defendant Cornell Prince in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

State complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, Defense, and Defendant.  Additional statement by Kathy S.

The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 10 years, concurrent to Washington County case 14CM1184 but consecutive to any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 5 years with credit for 168 days time served.
The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 5 years.

Conditions of Extended Supervision to be determined by the Dept. of Corrections, but to include:

*
*Mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*No contact with the victims:  Debra P., Andrea B., Guardian Credit Union and the co-actor:  Briean Vance.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Obtain high school diploma or GED.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.

Restitution is ordered in the amount of $2690.93 to be paid to Guardian Credit Union,  joint and several with Briean Vance 15CF2282.

- Defendant ordered to submit a DNA sample if not already done.
- Defendant advised that he may never again possess firearms or weapons.
- Civil rights suspended until reinstated.  Order received and filed.
- Pay all costs, restitution and surcharges, including the mandatory DNA surcharge, by DOC out of up to 25% prison funds and wages, any balance as a condition of ES.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.
- Defendant does qualify for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program after serving 4 years initial confinement in this case.

Appeal rights given.
- Received and filed:  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence; Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
Received and filed on behalf of the defendant.

Defendant Cornell Prince in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Defendant Cornell Prince in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.  Firearms/body armour warning given.  Voting admonishment given.  DNA notification given.  Any restitution will be determined at sentencing.  Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending sentencing.   Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 26.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.
